{"author":{"id":"cc8322a500b8739c77faac347808f6026d9ccb7880d0aaa7ad76754163cd7fdb"},"ops":[{"type":1,"timestamp":1782568927,"nonce":"1gSkFj7tJ9Ot9GHHrxzKE1uv5Pw=","kind":"plan","title":"Slice 2 — Labels (Classification) Implementation Plan"},{"type":3,"timestamp":1782568927,"nonce":"87W0KLRPqVrRH7oGwlj3je0B+lw=","body":"# Slice 2 — Labels (Classification) Implementation Plan\n\n\u003e **For agentic workers:** REQUIRED SUB-SKILL: Use superpowers:subagent-driven-development (recommended) or superpowers:executing-plans to implement this plan task-by-task. Steps use checkbox (`- [ ]`) syntax for tracking.\n\n**Goal:** Give entries a multi-valued, orthogonal **labels** facet — `kref add --label`, `kref label add|rm`, and `kref list --label` — so organization stops being overloaded onto the visibility tier.\n\n**Architecture:** Two new operations (`AddLabel`/`RemoveLabel`) on the existing `entity/dag`, mirroring `AddLink`/`RemoveLink`; an add/remove **set CRDT** (concurrent label changes always merge). `Snapshot` gains `Labels []string` (a sorted set). Store methods mirror `SetStatus`; the CLI commands are thin `emit` adapters. Labels render compactly in `list` and on a line in `show`.\n\n**Tech Stack:** Go 1.26.4, cobra, ginkgo/gomega, git-bug `entity/dag`. No new dependencies.\n\n**Spec:** `docs/dev/specs/2026-06-20-unified-entry-model-design.md` §4.2.\n\n---\n\n## Critical compatibility note\n\n`OperationType` values are serialized into stored operations. **New op types MUST be appended to the END of the `OperationType` iota** (after `RestoreOp`) — inserting in the middle would renumber existing types and corrupt the deserialization of already-stored entries.\n\n## Decisions (locked)\n\n- Labels are **free-form** strings; a `prefix:value` convention (`area:auth`, `project:kref`) is encouraged but not enforced.\n- `Snapshot.Labels` is a **sorted set** (dedup + `sort.Strings` on apply) for deterministic display and merge.\n- `kref list --label X --label Y` is **AND** (entry must carry every requested label).\n- Labels render: appended compactly to the title in `list` (`… Title  [area:auth spec]`) and as a `Labels:` line in `show`. No color (labels are not a safety signal).\n\n## File Structure\n\n- **Modify** `internal/entry/operations.go` — `AddLabelOp`/`RemoveLabelOp` (appended to iota), `AddLabel`/`RemoveLabel` ops, unmarshaler cases.\n- **Modify** `internal/entry/snapshot.go` — `Labels []string` field.\n- **Modify** `internal/entry/operations_test.go` — Apply tests (add/dedup/sort/remove).\n- **Modify** `internal/store/store.go` — `AddLabel`/`RemoveLabel` methods; `ListFilter.Labels` + filter.\n- **Modify** `internal/store/store_test.go` — store label tests.\n- **Modify** `cmd/kref/commands.go` — `add --label`; `newLabelCmd`; `list --label`.\n- **Modify** `cmd/kref/main.go` — register `newLabelCmd`.\n- **Modify** `internal/render/render.go` — labels in `List` rows and `Show`.\n- **Modify** `internal/render/render_test.go` — render label tests.\n- **Modify** `cmd/kref/cli_test.go` — CLI specs.\n- **Modify** `README.md`, `CHANGELOG.md`.\n\nSequencing: ops/snapshot (Task 1) → store (Task 2) → render (Task 3) → CLI add/label/list (Tasks 4–5) → docs/verify (Task 6).\n\n---\n\n## Task 1: Label operations + `Snapshot.Labels`\n\n**Files:**\n- Modify: `internal/entry/operations.go`\n- Modify: `internal/entry/snapshot.go`\n- Modify: `internal/entry/operations_test.go`\n\n- [ ] **Step 1: Add the `Labels` field to the snapshot**\n\nIn `internal/entry/snapshot.go`, add to the `Snapshot` struct immediately after the `Links []Link` line:\n\n```go\n\tLabels         []string  `json:\"labels\"`\n```\n\n- [ ] **Step 2: Write the failing op Apply tests**\n\nAppend to `internal/entry/operations_test.go`:\n\nThe existing op tests build an author with `newAuthor(newTestRepo())` (see the `SetTitle`/`Tombstone` specs at the top of the file) — reuse that exact pattern; the Apply tests need only the author, not a stored entity.\n\n```go\nvar _ = Describe(\"Label operations\", func() {\n\tIt(\"AddLabel adds, dedups, and keeps the set sorted\", func() {\n\t\tauthor := newAuthor(newTestRepo())\n\t\ts := \u0026entry.Snapshot{}\n\t\tentry.NewAddLabel(author, \"spec\").Apply(s)\n\t\tentry.NewAddLabel(author, \"area:auth\").Apply(s)\n\t\tentry.NewAddLabel(author, \"spec\").Apply(s) // dup\n\t\tExpect(s.Labels).To(Equal([]string{\"area:auth\", \"spec\"}))\n\t})\n\tIt(\"RemoveLabel removes a single label\", func() {\n\t\tauthor := newAuthor(newTestRepo())\n\t\ts := \u0026entry.Snapshot{Labels: []string{\"area:auth\", \"spec\"}}\n\t\tentry.NewRemoveLabel(author, \"spec\").Apply(s)\n\t\tExpect(s.Labels).To(Equal([]string{\"area:auth\"}))\n\t})\n\tIt(\"AddLabel validates a non-empty label\", func() {\n\t\tauthor := newAuthor(newTestRepo())\n\t\tExpect(entry.NewAddLabel(author, \"\").Validate()).To(HaveOccurred())\n\t\tExpect(entry.NewAddLabel(author, \"ok\").Validate()).To(Succeed())\n\t})\n})\n```\n\n- [ ] **Step 3: Run the tests to verify they fail**\n\nRun: `GOTOOLCHAIN=auto go test ./internal/entry/ 2\u003e\u00261 | tail -6`\nExpected: FAIL — `undefined: entry.NewAddLabel` / `entry.NewRemoveLabel`.\n\n- [ ] **Step 4: Append the op types to the iota**\n\nIn `internal/entry/operations.go`, the `OperationType` iota currently ends with `RestoreOp`. Append two new values **at the end** (preserving all existing values):\n\n```go\n\tRestoreOp\n\tAddLabelOp\n\tRemoveLabelOp\n)\n```\n\n(Change only by adding the two lines before the closing `)`; do not reorder existing entries.)\n\n- [ ] **Step 5: Implement the ops**\n\nAdd `\"sort\"` to `operations.go`'s import block. Append the operations (mirroring `AddLink`/`RemoveLink`):\n\n```go\n// AddLabel adds a label to the entry's label set.\ntype AddLabel struct {\n\tdag.OpBase\n\tLabel string `json:\"label\"`\n}\n\nfunc NewAddLabel(author identity.Interface, label string) *AddLabel {\n\treturn \u0026AddLabel{OpBase: dag.NewOpBase(AddLabelOp, author, time.Now().Unix()), Label: label}\n}\nfunc (op *AddLabel) Id() entity.Id { return dag.IdOperation(op, \u0026op.OpBase) }\nfunc (op *AddLabel) Validate() error {\n\tif op.Label == \"\" {\n\t\treturn fmt.Errorf(\"label required\")\n\t}\n\treturn op.OpBase.Validate(op, AddLabelOp)\n}\nfunc (op *AddLabel) Apply(s *Snapshot) {\n\tfor _, l := range s.Labels {\n\t\tif l == op.Label {\n\t\t\treturn\n\t\t}\n\t}\n\ts.Labels = append(s.Labels, op.Label)\n\tsort.Strings(s.Labels)\n\ts.UpdatedAt = op.Time()\n}\n\n// RemoveLabel removes a label from the entry's label set.\ntype RemoveLabel struct {\n\tdag.OpBase\n\tLabel string `json:\"label\"`\n}\n\nfunc NewRemoveLabel(author identity.Interface, label string) *RemoveLabel {\n\treturn \u0026RemoveLabel{OpBase: dag.NewOpBase(RemoveLabelOp, author, time.Now().Unix()), Label: label}\n}\nfunc (op *RemoveLabel) Id() entity.Id   { return dag.IdOperation(op, \u0026op.OpBase) }\nfunc (op *RemoveLabel) Validate() error { return op.OpBase.Validate(op, RemoveLabelOp) }\nfunc (op *RemoveLabel) Apply(s *Snapshot) {\n\tout := s.Labels[:0:0]\n\tfor _, l := range s.Labels {\n\t\tif l != op.Label {\n\t\t\tout = append(out, l)\n\t\t}\n\t}\n\ts.Labels = out\n\ts.UpdatedAt = op.Time()\n}\n```\n\n- [ ] **Step 6: Register the ops in the unmarshaler**\n\nIn `internal/entry/operations.go` `operationUnmarshaler`, add two cases before the `default:`:\n\n```go\n\tcase AddLabelOp:\n\t\top = \u0026AddLabel{}\n\tcase RemoveLabelOp:\n\t\top = \u0026RemoveLabel{}\n```\n\n- [ ] **Step 7: Run the tests to verify they pass**\n\nRun: `GOTOOLCHAIN=auto go test ./internal/entry/ 2\u003e\u00261 | tail -5`\nExpected: PASS. Also `GOTOOLCHAIN=auto go vet ./internal/entry/`.\n\n- [ ] **Step 8: Commit**\n\n```bash\ngit add internal/entry/operations.go internal/entry/snapshot.go internal/entry/operations_test.go\ngit commit -m \"feat(entry): AddLabel/RemoveLabel ops + Snapshot.Labels (sorted set)\"\n```\n\n---\n\n## Task 2: Store label methods + `ListFilter.Labels`\n\n**Files:**\n- Modify: `internal/store/store.go`\n- Modify: `internal/store/store_test.go`\n\n- [ ] **Step 1: Write the failing store tests**\n\nAppend to `internal/store/store_test.go`:\n\n```go\nvar _ = Describe(\"Store labels\", func() {\n\tIt(\"adds, removes, and filters by labels (AND)\", func() {\n\t\tdir := gitRepo()\n\t\ts, err := Init(dir, \"Tester\", \"t@e.com\")\n\t\tExpect(err).NotTo(HaveOccurred())\n\t\tDeferCleanup(func() { _ = s.Close() })\n\t\tid, err := s.Add(entry.TierShared, \"spec\", \"T\", \"b\")\n\t\tExpect(err).NotTo(HaveOccurred())\n\n\t\tExpect(s.AddLabel(id, \"area:auth\")).To(Succeed())\n\t\tExpect(s.AddLabel(id, \"spec\")).To(Succeed())\n\t\tsnap, err := s.Get(id)\n\t\tExpect(err).NotTo(HaveOccurred())\n\t\tExpect(snap.Labels).To(Equal([]string{\"area:auth\", \"spec\"}))\n\n\t\t// AND semantics: both labels match; a non-present label excludes.\n\t\tboth, err := s.List(ListFilter{Labels: []string{\"area:auth\", \"spec\"}})\n\t\tExpect(err).NotTo(HaveOccurred())\n\t\tExpect(both).To(HaveLen(1))\n\t\tnone, err := s.List(ListFilter{Labels: []string{\"area:auth\", \"missing\"}})\n\t\tExpect(err).NotTo(HaveOccurred())\n\t\tExpect(none).To(HaveLen(0))\n\n\t\tExpect(s.RemoveLabel(id, \"spec\")).To(Succeed())\n\t\tsnap, err = s.Get(id)\n\t\tExpect(err).NotTo(HaveOccurred())\n\t\tExpect(snap.Labels).To(Equal([]string{\"area:auth\"}))\n\t})\n})\n```\n\n- [ ] **Step 2: Run the store tests to verify they fail**\n\nRun: `GOTOOLCHAIN=auto go test ./internal/store/ 2\u003e\u00261 | tail -6`\nExpected: FAIL — `s.AddLabel undefined` and `unknown field 'Labels'`.\n\n- [ ] **Step 3: Add the store methods**\n\nAdd to `internal/store/store.go`, mirroring `SetStatus` (place next to it):\n\n```go\n// AddLabel adds a label to an entry, searching all tiers.\nfunc (s *Store) AddLabel(id entity.Id, label string) error {\n\tfor _, t := range entry.AllTiers() {\n\t\te, err := entry.Read(s.repo, t, id)\n\t\tif err != nil {\n\t\t\tif entity.IsErrNotFound(err) {\n\t\t\t\tcontinue\n\t\t\t}\n\t\t\treturn fmt.Errorf(\"read %s in tier %s: %w\", id, t, err)\n\t\t}\n\t\te.Append(entry.NewAddLabel(s.author, label))\n\t\treturn e.Commit(s.repo)\n\t}\n\treturn fmt.Errorf(\"entry %s not found\", id)\n}\n\n// RemoveLabel removes a label from an entry, searching all tiers.\nfunc (s *Store) RemoveLabel(id entity.Id, label string) error {\n\tfor _, t := range entry.AllTiers() {\n\t\te, err := entry.Read(s.repo, t, id)\n\t\tif err != nil {\n\t\t\tif entity.IsErrNotFound(err) {\n\t\t\t\tcontinue\n\t\t\t}\n\t\t\treturn fmt.Errorf(\"read %s in tier %s: %w\", id, t, err)\n\t\t}\n\t\te.Append(entry.NewRemoveLabel(s.author, label))\n\t\treturn e.Commit(s.repo)\n\t}\n\treturn fmt.Errorf(\"entry %s not found\", id)\n}\n```\n\n- [ ] **Step 4: Add `Labels` to `ListFilter` and filter on it**\n\nAdd the field to the `ListFilter` struct:\n\n```go\n\tLabels        []string\n```\n\nIn `List`, immediately after the `Search` filter block and before `out = append(out, snap)`, add:\n\n```go\n\t\t\tif len(f.Labels) \u003e 0 {\n\t\t\t\thave := make(map[string]bool, len(snap.Labels))\n\t\t\t\tfor _, l := range snap.Labels {\n\t\t\t\t\thave[l] = true\n\t\t\t\t}\n\t\t\t\tmissing := false\n\t\t\t\tfor _, want := range f.Labels {\n\t\t\t\t\tif !have[want] {\n\t\t\t\t\t\tmissing = true\n\t\t\t\t\t\tbreak\n\t\t\t\t\t}\n\t\t\t\t}\n\t\t\t\tif missing {\n\t\t\t\t\tcontinue\n\t\t\t\t}\n\t\t\t}\n```\n\n- [ ] **Step 5: Run the store tests to verify they pass**\n\nRun: `GOTOOLCHAIN=auto go test ./internal/store/ 2\u003e\u00261 | tail -5`\nExpected: PASS.\n\n- [ ] **Step 6: Commit**\n\n```bash\ngit add internal/store/store.go internal/store/store_test.go\ngit commit -m \"feat(store): AddLabel/RemoveLabel + ListFilter.Labels (AND)\"\n```\n\n---\n\n## Task 3: Render labels in `list` and `show`\n\n**Files:**\n- Modify: `internal/render/render.go`\n- Modify: `internal/render/render_test.go`\n\n- [ ] **Step 1: Write the failing render tests**\n\nAppend to `internal/render/render_test.go` (the `snap` helper there builds `*entry.Snapshot`; set `Labels` directly on a literal):\n\n```go\nvar _ = Describe(\"labels rendering\", func() {\n\tIt(\"appends labels to the list row title\", func() {\n\t\tvar b bytes.Buffer\n\t\tit := \u0026entry.Snapshot{ID: entity.Id(\"a\"), Tier: \"shared\", Kind: \"spec\", Status: \"open\", Title: \"Auth\", Labels: []string{\"area:auth\", \"spec\"}}\n\t\trender.List(\u0026b, []*entry.Snapshot{it}, false)\n\t\tExpect(b.String()).To(ContainSubstring(\"Auth  [area:auth spec]\"))\n\t})\n\tIt(\"shows a Labels line in the detail view\", func() {\n\t\tvar b bytes.Buffer\n\t\ts := \u0026entry.Snapshot{ID: entity.Id(\"a\"), Tier: \"shared\", Status: \"open\", Title: \"Auth\", Labels: []string{\"area:auth\", \"spec\"}}\n\t\trender.Show(\u0026b, s, false)\n\t\tExpect(b.String()).To(ContainSubstring(\"Labels: area:auth, spec\"))\n\t})\n\tIt(\"omits the Labels line when there are none\", func() {\n\t\tvar b bytes.Buffer\n\t\ts := \u0026entry.Snapshot{ID: entity.Id(\"a\"), Tier: \"shared\", Status: \"open\", Title: \"Auth\"}\n\t\trender.Show(\u0026b, s, false)\n\t\tExpect(b.String()).NotTo(ContainSubstring(\"Labels:\"))\n\t})\n})\n```\n\n- [ ] **Step 2: Run the render tests to verify they fail**\n\nRun: `GOTOOLCHAIN=auto go test ./internal/render/ 2\u003e\u00261 | tail -8`\nExpected: FAIL — list row has no `[...]`, show has no `Labels:` line.\n\n- [ ] **Step 3: Append labels to the list row title**\n\nIn `internal/render/render.go` `List`, find the row loop where `title` is built:\n\n```go\n\t\ttitle := it.Title\n\t\tif it.Deleted {\n\t\t\ttitle += \"  (deleted)\"\n\t\t}\n```\n\nAdd a labels suffix immediately after that block (and ensure `strings` is imported in render.go — it is not yet, so add `\"strings\"` to the import block):\n\n```go\n\t\tif len(it.Labels) \u003e 0 {\n\t\t\ttitle += \"  [\" + strings.Join(it.Labels, \" \") + \"]\"\n\t\t}\n```\n\n- [ ] **Step 4: Add the Labels line to `Show`**\n\nReplace the `Show` function body so it conditionally prints a `Labels:` line between the header and the body. The current body is:\n\n```go\n\tfmt.Fprintf(w, \"%s [%s/%s] %s — by %s \u003c%s\u003e\\n\\n%s\\n\",\n\t\tsnap.ID, tierWord(snap.Tier, color), snap.Status, snap.Title,\n\t\tsnap.CreatedBy, snap.CreatedByEmail, snap.Body)\n```\n\nReplace it with:\n\n```go\n\tfmt.Fprintf(w, \"%s [%s/%s] %s — by %s \u003c%s\u003e\\n\",\n\t\tsnap.ID, tierWord(snap.Tier, color), snap.Status, snap.Title,\n\t\tsnap.CreatedBy, snap.CreatedByEmail)\n\tif len(snap.Labels) \u003e 0 {\n\t\tfmt.Fprintf(w, \"Labels: %s\\n\", strings.Join(snap.Labels, \", \"))\n\t}\n\tfmt.Fprintf(w, \"\\n%s\\n\", snap.Body)\n```\n\n- [ ] **Step 5: Run the render tests to verify they pass**\n\nRun: `GOTOOLCHAIN=auto go test ./internal/render/ 2\u003e\u00261 | tail -5`\nExpected: PASS. Run `GOTOOLCHAIN=auto go vet ./internal/render/`.\n\n\u003e Note: `cmd/kref`'s existing `show` specs assert substrings like `[private/open]`, `by Tester \u003ct@t.io\u003e`, and body text — all still present after this change (the header line and body are unchanged in content; only a conditional middle line is added). Confirm in Task 6's full run.\n\n- [ ] **Step 6: Commit**\n\n```bash\ngit add internal/render/render.go internal/render/render_test.go\ngit commit -m \"feat(render): show labels in list rows and the detail view\"\n```\n\n---\n\n## Task 4: `kref add --label` and `kref label add|rm`\n\n**Files:**\n- Modify: `cmd/kref/commands.go` (`newAddCmd`, new `newLabelCmd`)\n- Modify: `cmd/kref/main.go`\n- Modify: `cmd/kref/cli_test.go`\n\n- [ ] **Step 1: Write the failing CLI specs**\n\nAppend to `cmd/kref/cli_test.go`:\n\n```go\nvar _ = Describe(\"labels CLI\", func() {\n\taddID := func(dir string, args ...string) string {\n\t\tGinkgoHelper()\n\t\trun(\"--dir\", dir, \"init\", \"--name\", \"T\", \"--email\", \"t@e.com\")\n\t\tout := run(append([]string{\"--dir\", dir, \"add\", \"--title\", \"L\", \"--body\", \"b\", \"--json\"}, args...)...)\n\t\tvar a struct {\n\t\t\tID string `json:\"id\"`\n\t\t}\n\t\tExpect(json.Unmarshal([]byte(out), \u0026a)).To(Succeed())\n\t\treturn a.ID\n\t}\n\n\tIt(\"attaches labels at add time\", func() {\n\t\tdir := gitRepo()\n\t\tid := addID(dir, \"--label\", \"area:auth\", \"--label\", \"spec\")\n\t\tExpect(run(\"--dir\", dir, \"show\", id)).To(ContainSubstring(\"Labels: area:auth, spec\"))\n\t})\n\tIt(\"adds and removes labels via kref label\", func() {\n\t\tdir := gitRepo()\n\t\tid := addID(dir)\n\t\tExpect(run(\"--dir\", dir, \"label\", \"add\", id, \"x\", \"y\")).To(ContainSubstring(\"labeled\"))\n\t\tExpect(run(\"--dir\", dir, \"show\", id)).To(ContainSubstring(\"Labels: x, y\"))\n\t\trun(\"--dir\", dir, \"label\", \"rm\", id, \"x\")\n\t\tshown := run(\"--dir\", dir, \"show\", id)\n\t\tExpect(shown).To(ContainSubstring(\"Labels: y\"))\n\t\tExpect(shown).NotTo(ContainSubstring(\"Labels: x, y\"))\n\t})\n})\n```\n\n- [ ] **Step 2: Run the specs to verify they fail**\n\nRun: `GOTOOLCHAIN=auto go test ./cmd/kref/ 2\u003e\u00261 | tail -8`\nExpected: FAIL — `unknown flag: --label` and `unknown command \"label\"`.\n\n- [ ] **Step 3: Add `--label` to `add`**\n\nIn `cmd/kref/commands.go` `newAddCmd`: add a `labels` variable and flag, and apply each label after the entry is created. Change the `var` line to include `labels`:\n\n```go\n\tvar kind, title, body, tier string\n\tvar labels []string\n```\n\nAfter the existing `id, err := s.Add(t, kind, title, body)` / error check, and before `snap, err := s.Get(id)`, insert:\n\n```go\n\t\t\tfor _, l := range labels {\n\t\t\t\tif err := s.AddLabel(id, l); err != nil {\n\t\t\t\t\treturn err\n\t\t\t\t}\n\t\t\t}\n```\n\nRegister the flag with the others:\n\n```go\n\tc.Flags().StringArrayVar(\u0026labels, \"label\", nil, \"label to attach (repeatable)\")\n```\n\n- [ ] **Step 4: Add `newLabelCmd`**\n\nAdd to `cmd/kref/commands.go` (parent `label` with `add`/`rm` subcommands, mirroring `newRemoteCmd`'s structure):\n\n```go\nfunc newLabelCmd(dir *string) *cobra.Command {\n\tc := \u0026cobra.Command{Use: \"label\", Short: \"Add or remove entry labels\"}\n\tmk := func(use, verb string, fn func(*store.Store, entity.Id, string) error) *cobra.Command {\n\t\treturn \u0026cobra.Command{\n\t\t\tUse:   use,\n\t\t\tShort: verb + \" one or more labels on an entry\",\n\t\t\tArgs:  cobra.MinimumNArgs(2),\n\t\t\tRunE: func(cmd *cobra.Command, args []string) error {\n\t\t\t\ts, err := store.Open(*dir)\n\t\t\t\tif err != nil {\n\t\t\t\t\treturn err\n\t\t\t\t}\n\t\t\t\tdefer s.Close()\n\t\t\t\tid, err := s.Resolve(args[0])\n\t\t\t\tif err != nil {\n\t\t\t\t\treturn err\n\t\t\t\t}\n\t\t\t\tfor _, l := range args[1:] {\n\t\t\t\t\tif err := fn(s, id, l); err != nil {\n\t\t\t\t\t\treturn err\n\t\t\t\t\t}\n\t\t\t\t}\n\t\t\t\tsnap, err := s.Get(id)\n\t\t\t\tif err != nil {\n\t\t\t\t\treturn err\n\t\t\t\t}\n\t\t\t\treturn emit(cmd,\n\t\t\t\t\tfunc(w io.Writer, _ bool) {\n\t\t\t\t\t\tfmt.Fprintf(w, \"%s %s  [%s]\\n\", verb, render.ShortID(id), strings.Join(snap.Labels, \" \"))\n\t\t\t\t\t},\n\t\t\t\t\tmap[string]any{\"status\": verb, \"id\": id.String(), \"labels\": snap.Labels})\n\t\t\t},\n\t\t}\n\t}\n\tc.AddCommand(\n\t\tmk(\"add \u003cid\u003e \u003clabel\u003e...\", \"labeled\", (*store.Store).AddLabel),\n\t\tmk(\"rm \u003cid\u003e \u003clabel\u003e...\", \"unlabeled\", (*store.Store).RemoveLabel),\n\t)\n\treturn c\n}\n```\n\n(`entity` is NOT currently imported in `commands.go` — add `\"github.com/git-bug/git-bug/entity\"` to its import block for the `entity.Id` parameter type in the `fn` signature.)\n\n- [ ] **Step 5: Register `label` in `main.go`**\n\nIn `cmd/kref/main.go`, in the core group (next to `newListCmd`), add:\n\n```go\n\taddTo(\"core\", newLabelCmd(\u0026dir))\n```\n\n- [ ] **Step 6: Run the suite to verify it passes**\n\nRun: `GOTOOLCHAIN=auto go test ./cmd/kref/ 2\u003e\u00261 | tail -8`\nExpected: PASS. Run `GOTOOLCHAIN=auto go vet ./cmd/kref/`.\n\n- [ ] **Step 7: Commit**\n\n```bash\ngit add cmd/kref/commands.go cmd/kref/main.go cmd/kref/cli_test.go\ngit commit -m \